This paper discusses a privacy attack against machine learning models, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the attack across different subgroups, which involves analyzing the performance of machine learning models (cs.LG) and potentially using techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The attack may also involve analyzing image data (cs.CV) or other types of data, and the paper discusses the potential impact on privacy-sensitive domains (cs.SI).
